Apply the rule $(x, y) \to (-y, x)$ to each vertex:
$$
 A(1, 0) &\to A'(0, 1) \\
 B(4, 0) &\to B'(0, 4) \\
 C(2, 3) &\to C'(-3, 2)
$$

center
tikzpicture[scale=0.65]
 % Grid
 (-4,-1) grid (5,5);
 (-4,0) – (5.5,0) node[right] {$x$};
 (0,-1) – (0,5.5) node[above] {$y$};

 % Original triangle
 ll[AtlasTeal!20] (1,0) – (4,0) – (2,3) – cycle;
 (1,0) – (4,0) – (2,3) – cycle;
 ll[AtlasTeal] (1,0) circle (3pt) node[below] {$A$};
 ll[AtlasTeal] (4,0) circle (3pt) node[below] {$B$};
 ll[AtlasTeal] (2,3) circle (3pt) node[above right] {$C$};

 % Image triangle
 ll[AtlasWarm!20] (0,1) – (0,4) – (-3,2) – cycle;
 (0,1) – (0,4) – (-3,2) – cycle;
 ll[AtlasWarm] (0,1) circle (3pt) node[right] {$A'$};
 ll[AtlasWarm] (0,4) circle (3pt) node[right] {$B'$};
 ll[AtlasWarm] (-3,2) circle (3pt) node[left] {$C'$};

 % Center
 ll[black] (0,0) circle (3pt) node[below left] {$O$};

 % Rotation arc
 (1.5,0) arc (0:90:1.5);
tikzpicture
center

Apply $(x, y) \to (-x, -y)$:
$$
 P(1, 1) &\to P'(-1, -1) \\
 Q(4, 1) &\to Q'(-4, -1) \\
 R(4, 3) &\to R'(-4, -3) \\
 S(1, 3) &\to S'(-1, -3)
$$

center
tikzpicture[scale=0.6]
 % Grid
 (-5,-4) grid (5,4);
 (-5,0) – (5.5,0) node[right] {$x$};
 (0,-4) – (0,4.5) node[above] {$y$};

 % Original rectangle
 ll[AtlasTeal!20] (1,1) rectangle (4,3);
 (1,1) rectangle (4,3);
 ll[AtlasTeal] (1,1) circle (3pt) node[below right] {$P$};
 ll[AtlasTeal] (4,1) circle (3pt) node[below right] {$Q$};
 ll[AtlasTeal] (4,3) circle (3pt) node[above right] {$R$};
 ll[AtlasTeal] (1,3) circle (3pt) node[above left] {$S$};

 % Image rectangle
 ll[AtlasWarm!20] (-1,-1) rectangle (-4,-3);
 (-1,-1) rectangle (-4,-3);
 ll[AtlasWarm] (-1,-1) circle (3pt) node[above right] {$P'$};
 ll[AtlasWarm] (-4,-1) circle (3pt) node[above left] {$Q'$};
 ll[AtlasWarm] (-4,-3) circle (3pt) node[below left] {$R'$};
 ll[AtlasWarm] (-1,-3) circle (3pt) node[below right] {$S'$};

 % Center
 ll[black] (0,0) circle (3pt) node[above right] {$O$};
tikzpicture
center

**Step 1:** Translate so $C$ becomes the origin:
\[
 A - C = (5 - 2, 2 - 1) = (3, 1)
\]

**Step 2:** Apply $90°$ rotation about origin using $(x, y) \to (-y, x)$:
\[
 (3, 1) \to (-1, 3)
\]

**Step 3:** Translate back by adding $C$:
\[
 (-1 + 2, 3 + 1) = (1, 4)
\]

The image is $A'(1, 4)$.

center
tikzpicture[scale=0.7]
 % Grid
 (-1,-1) grid (7,6);
 (-1,0) – (7.5,0) node[right] {$x$};
 (0,-1) – (0,6.5) node[above] {$y$};

 % Center of rotation
 ll[AtlasSage] (2,1) circle (4pt);
 at (2,0.7) {$C(2,1)$};

 % Original point
 ll[AtlasTeal] (5,2) circle (4pt);
 at (5.2,2) {$A(5, 2)$};

 % Image point
 ll[AtlasWarm] (1,4) circle (4pt);
 at (0.8,4) {$A'(1, 4)$};

 % Arc showing rotation
 (4.2,1.8) arc (18.43:108.43:2.24);
 at (2.5,3.5) {$90°$};

 % Radii
 (2,1) – (5,2);
 (2,1) – (1,4);
tikzpicture
